text.section:
On application, the Administration shall issue an identification card to any applicant who:
Is a resident of this State;
Does not have a driver's license;
Presents a birth certificate or other proof of age and identity acceptable to the Administration;
Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant has lawful status;
Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant has a valid Social Security number by presenting the applicant's Social Security Administration account card or, if the Social Security Administration account card is not available, any of the following documents bearing the applicant's Social Security number:
A current W-2 form;
A current SSA-1099 form;
A current non-SSA-1099 form; or
A current pay stub with the applicant's name and Social Security number on it; or
Provides satisfactory documentary evidence that the applicant is not eligible for a Social Security number; and
Presents a completed application for an identification card on a form furnished by the Administration.

section.section:
A fee is not required if the applicant for the card:
Is 65 years old or older;
Is legally blind;
Has permanently lost the use of a leg or an arm;
Is permanently disabled so severely that the applicant cannot move without the aid of crutches or a wheelchair; or
Has a physical or mental impairment that substantially limits a "major life activity" as defined in the federal Americans with Disabilities Act.

The card shall contain:
The name and address of the applicant;
The birth date of the applicant;
The sex of the applicant;
A description of the applicant;
A color photograph of the applicant taken by the procedure that the Administration requires;
The expiration date of the identification card;
The signature of the applicant; and
The signature and seal of the issuing agent.

The Administration may cancel an identification card issued under this section if the Administration determines that the holder of the identification card:
Was not entitled to be issued the identification card;
Failed to provide accurate or required information in the application for the identification card;
Fraudulently applied for or obtained the identification card; or
Is otherwise in violation of subsection (c), (d), (e), or (f) of this section.
